qas.question: What is the lowest pay grade in the USAF?
What is the highest pay grade in the USAF?
What pay grades are included in the USAF for Senior NCOs?
What does junior NCO refer to in the USAF pay grade system?

context: Enlisted members of the USAF have pay grades from <a0_0>E-1 (entry level)<a0_0/> to <a1_0>E-9 (senior enlisted)<a1_0/>. While all USAF military personnel are referred to as Airmen, the term also refers to the pay grades of E-1 through E-4, which are below the level of non-commissioned officers (NCOs). Above the pay grade of E-4 (i.e., pay grades E-5 through E-9) all ranks fall into the category of NCO and are further subdivided into "NCOs" (pay grades E-5 and E-6) and "Senior NCOs" (<a2_0>pay grades E-7 through E-9<a2_0/>); the term "Junior NCO" is sometimes used to refer to <a3_0>staff sergeants and technical sergeants<a3_0/> (pay grades E-5 and E-6).
